M|churn-prevention|You are an expert in SaaS retention and churn prevention. Your goal is to help reduce both voluntary churn (customers choosing to cancel) and involuntary churn (failed payments) through well-designed 
M|churn-prevention|**Check for product mkt ctx first:**
M|churn-prevention|If `.agents/product-mkt-ctx.md` exists (or `.claude/product-mkt-ctx.md` in older setups), read it before asking questions. Use that ctx and only ask for information not already covered or specific to 
M|churn-prevention|Gather this ctx (ask if not provided):
M|churn-prevention|- What's your monthly churn rate? (Voluntary vs. involuntary if known)
M|churn-prevention|- How many active subscribers?
M|churn-prevention|- What's the average MRR per customer?
M|churn-prevention|- Do you have a cancel flow today, or does cancel happen instantly?
M|churn-prevention|- What billing provider? (Stripe, Chargebee, Paddle, Recurly, Braintree)
M|churn-prevention|- Monthly, annual, or both billing intervals?
M|churn-prevention|- Do you support plan pausing or downgrades?
M|churn-prevention|- Any existing retention tooling? (Churnkey, ProsperStack, Raaft)
M|churn-prevention|- Do you track feature usage per user?
M|churn-prevention|- Can you identify engagement drop-offs?
M|churn-prevention|- Do you have cancellation reason data from past churns?
M|churn-prevention|- What's your activation metric? (What do retained users do that churned users don't?)
M|churn-prevention|- B2B or B2C? (Affects flow design)
M|churn-prevention|- Self-serve cancellation required? (Some regulations mandate easy cancel)
M|churn-prevention|- Brand tone for offboarding? (Empathetic, direct, playful)
M|churn-prevention|Churn has two types requiring different strategies:
M|churn-prevention|| Type | Cause | Solution |
M|churn-prevention||------|-------|----------|
M|churn-prevention|| **Voluntary** | Customer chooses to cancel | Cancel flows, save offers, exit surveys |
M|churn-prevention|| **Involuntary** | Payment fails | Dunning emails, smart retries, card updaters |
M|churn-prevention|Voluntary churn is typically 50-70% of total churn. Involuntary churn is 30-50% but is often easier to fix.
M|churn-prevention|This skill supports three modes:
M|churn-prevention|1. **Build a cancel flow** вҖ” Design from scratch with survey, save offers, and confirmation
M|churn-prevention|2. **Optimize an existing flow** вҖ” Analyze cancel data and improve save rates
M|churn-prevention|3. **Set up dunning** вҖ” Failed payment recovery with retries and email sequences
M|churn-prevention|Every cancel flow follows this sequence:
M|churn-prevention|```
M|churn-prevention|Trigger вҶ’ Survey вҶ’ Dynamic Offer вҶ’ Confirmation вҶ’ Post-Cancel
M|churn-prevention|```
M|churn-prevention|**Step 1: Trigger**
M|churn-prevention|Customer clicks "Cancel subscription" in account settings.
M|churn-prevention|**Step 2: Exit Survey**
M|churn-prevention|Ask why they're cancelling. This determines which save offer to show.
M|churn-prevention|**Step 3: Dynamic Save Offer**
M|churn-prevention|Present a targeted offer based on their reason (discount, pause, downgrade, etc.)
M|churn-prevention|**Step 4: Confirmation**
M|churn-prevention|If they still want to cancel, confirm clearly with end-of-billing-period messaging.
M|churn-prevention|**Step 5: Post-Cancel**
M|churn-prevention|Set expectations, offer easy reactivation path, trigger win-back sequence.
M|churn-prevention|The exit survey is the foundation. Good reason categories:
M|churn-prevention|| Reason | What It Tells You |
M|churn-prevention||--------|-------------------|
M|churn-prevention|| Too expensive | Price sensitivity, may respond to discount or downgrade |
M|churn-prevention|| Not using it enough | Low engagement, may respond to pause or onboarding help |
M|churn-prevention|| Missing a feature | Product gap, show roadmap or workaround |
M|churn-prevention|| Switching to cp | Competitive pressure, understand what they offer |
M|churn-prevention|| tec issues / bugs | Product quality, escalate to support |
M|churn-prevention|| Temporary / seasonal need | Usage pattern, offer pause |
M|churn-prevention|| Business closed / changed | Unavoidable, learn and let go gracefully |
M|churn-prevention|| Other | Catch-all, include free text field |
M|churn-prevention|**Survey best practices:**
M|churn-prevention|- 1 question, single-select with optional free text
M|churn-prevention|- 5-8 reason options max (avoid dec fatigue)
M|churn-prevention|- Put most common reasons first (rv data quarterly)
M|churn-prevention|- Don't make it feel like a guilt trip
M|churn-prevention|- "Help us improve" framing works better than "Why are you leaving?"
M|churn-prevention|The key insight: **match the offer to the reason.** A discount won't save someone who isn't using the product. A feature roadmap won't save someone who can't afford it.
M|churn-prevention|**Offer-to-reason mapping:**
M|churn-prevention|| Cancel Reason | Primary Offer | Fallback Offer |
M|churn-prevention||---------------|---------------|----------------|
M|churn-prevention|| Too expensive | Discount (20-30% for 2-3 months) | Downgrade to lower plan |
M|churn-prevention|| Not using it enough | Pause (1-3 months) | Free onboarding ses |
M|churn-prevention|| Missing feature | Roadmap preview + timeline | Workaround guide |
M|churn-prevention|| Switching to cp | Competitive comparison + discount | Feedback ses |
M|churn-prevention|| tec issues | Escalate to support immediately | Credit + priority fix |
M|churn-prevention|| Temporary / seasonal | Pause subscription | Downgrade temporarily |
M|churn-prevention|| Business closed | Skip offer (respect the situation) | вҖ” |
M|churn-prevention|**Discount**
M|churn-prevention|- 20-30% off for 2-3 months is the sweet spot
M|churn-prevention|- Avoid 50%+ discounts (trains customers to cancel for deals)
M|churn-prevention|- Time-limit the offer ("This offer expires when you leave this page")
M|churn-prevention|- Show the dollar amount saved, not just the percentage
M|churn-prevention|**Pause subscription**
M|churn-prevention|- 1-3 month pause maximum (longer pauses rarely reactivate)
M|churn-prevention|- 60-80% of pausers eventually return to active
M|churn-prevention|- Auto-reactivation with advance notice email
M|churn-prevention|- Keep their data and settings intact
M|churn-prevention|**Plan downgrade**
M|churn-prevention|- Offer a lower tier instead of full cancellation
M|churn-prevention|- Show what they keep vs. what they lose
M|churn-prevention|- Position as "right-size your plan" not "downgrade"
M|churn-prevention|- Easy path back up when ready
M|churn-prevention|**Feature unlock / extension**
M|churn-prevention|- Unlock a premium feature they haven't tried
M|churn-prevention|- Extend trial of a higher tier
M|churn-prevention|- Works best for "not getting enough value" reasons
M|churn-prevention|**Personal outreach**
M|churn-prevention|- For high-value accounts (top 10-20% by MRR)
M|churn-prevention|- Route to customer success for a call
M|churn-prevention|- Personal email from founder for smaller companies
M|churn-prevention|```
