M|churn-prevention|**UI principles:**
M|churn-prevention|- Keep the "continue cancelling" option visible (no dark patterns)
M|churn-prevention|- One primary offer + one fallback, not a wall of options
M|churn-prevention|- Show specific dollar savings, not abstract percentages
M|churn-prevention|- Use the customer's name and account data when possible
M|churn-prevention|- Mobile-friendly (many cancellations happen on mobile)
M|churn-prevention|For detailed cancel flow patterns by industry and billing provider, see [references/cancel-flow-patterns.md](references/cancel-flow-patterns.md).
M|churn-prevention|The best save happens before the customer ever clicks "Cancel."
M|churn-prevention|Track these leading indicators of churn:
M|churn-prevention|| Signal | Risk Level | Timeframe |
M|churn-prevention||--------|-----------|-----------|
M|churn-prevention|| Login frequency drops 50%+ | High | 2-4 weeks before cancel |
M|churn-prevention|| Key feature usage stops | High | 1-3 weeks before cancel |
M|churn-prevention|| Support tickets spike then stop | High | 1-2 weeks before cancel |
M|churn-prevention|| Email open rates decline | Medium | 2-6 weeks before cancel |
M|churn-prevention|| Billing page visits increase | High | Days before cancel |
M|churn-prevention|| Team seats removed | High | 1-2 weeks before cancel |
M|churn-prevention|| Data export initiated | Critical | Days before cancel |
M|churn-prevention|| NPS score drops below 6 | Medium | 1-3 months before cancel |
M|churn-prevention|Build a simple health score (0-100) from weighted signals:
M|churn-prevention|```
M|churn-prevention|Health Score = (
M|churn-prevention|Login frequency score Г— 0.30 +
M|churn-prevention|Feature usage score   Г— 0.25 +
M|churn-prevention|Support sentiment     Г— 0.15 +
M|churn-prevention|Billing health        Г— 0.15 +
M|churn-prevention|Engagement score      Г— 0.15
M|churn-prevention|)
M|churn-prevention|```
M|churn-prevention|| Score | Status | Action |
M|churn-prevention||-------|--------|--------|
M|churn-prevention|| 80-100 | Healthy | Upsell opportunities |
M|churn-prevention|| 60-79 | Needs attention | Proactive check-in |
M|churn-prevention|| 40-59 | At risk | Intervention cg |
M|churn-prevention|| 0-39 | Critical | Personal outreach |
M|churn-prevention|**Before they think about cancelling:**
M|churn-prevention|| Trigger | Intervention |
M|churn-prevention||---------|-------------|
M|churn-prevention|| Usage drop >50% for 2 weeks | "We noticed you haven't used [feature]. Need help?" email |
M|churn-prevention|| Approaching plan limit | Upgrade nudge (not a wall вҖ” paywall-upgrade-cro handles this) |
M|churn-prevention|| No login for 14 days | Re-engagement email with recent product updates |
M|churn-prevention|| NPS detractor (0-6) | Personal follow-up within 24 hours |
M|churn-prevention|| Support ticket unresolved >48h | Escalation + proactive status update |
M|churn-prevention|| Annual renewal in 30 days | Value recap email + renewal confirmation |
M|churn-prevention|Failed payments cause 30-50% of all churn but are the most recoverable.
M|churn-prevention|```
M|churn-prevention|Pre-dunning вҶ’ Smart retry вҶ’ Dunning emails вҶ’ Grace period вҶ’ Hard cancel
M|churn-prevention|```
M|churn-prevention|- **Card expiry alerts**: Email 30, 15, and 7 days before card expires
M|churn-prevention|- **Backup payment method**: Prompt for a second payment method at signup
M|churn-prevention|- **Card updater services**: Visa/Mastercard auto-update programs (reduces hard declines 30-50%)
M|churn-prevention|- **Pre-billing notification**: Email 3-5 days before charge for annual plans
M|churn-prevention|Not all failures are the same. Retry str by decline type:
M|churn-prevention|| Decline Type | Examples | Retry str |
M|churn-prevention||-------------|----------|----------------|
M|churn-prevention|| Soft decline (temporary) | Insufficient funds, processor timeout | Retry 3-5 times over 7-10 days |
M|churn-prevention|| Hard decline (permanent) | Card stolen, account closed | Don't retry вҖ” ask for new card |
M|churn-prevention|| Authentication required | 3D Secure, SCA | Send customer to update payment |
M|churn-prevention|**Retry timing best practices:**
M|churn-prevention|- Retry 1: 24 hours after failure
M|churn-prevention|- Retry 2: 3 days after failure
M|churn-prevention|- Retry 3: 5 days after failure
M|churn-prevention|- Retry 4: 7 days after failure (with dunning email escalation)
M|churn-prevention|- After 4 retries: Hard cancel with reactivation path
M|churn-prevention|**Smart retry tip:** Retry on the day of the month the payment originally succeeded (if Day 1 worked before, retry on Day 1). Stripe Smart Retries handles this automatically.
M|churn-prevention|| Email | Timing | Tone | cnt |
M|churn-prevention||-------|--------|------|---------|
M|churn-prevention|| 1 | Day 0 (failure) | Friendly alert | "Your payment didn't go through. Update your card." |
M|churn-prevention|| 2 | Day 3 | Helpful reminder | "Quick reminder вҖ” update your payment to keep access." |
M|churn-prevention|| 3 | Day 7 | Urgency | "Your account will be paused in 3 days. Update now." |
M|churn-prevention|| 4 | Day 10 | Final warning | "Last chance to keep your account active." |
M|churn-prevention|**Dunning email best practices:**
M|churn-prevention|- Direct link to payment update page (no login required if possible)
M|churn-prevention|- Show what they'll lose (their data, their team's access)
M|churn-prevention|- Don't blame ("your payment failed" not "you failed to pay")
M|churn-prevention|- Include support contact for help
M|churn-prevention|- Plain text performs better than designed emails for dunning
M|churn-prevention|| Metric | Poor | Average | Good |
M|churn-prevention||--------|------|---------|------|
M|churn-prevention|| Soft decline recovery | <40% | 50-60% | 70%+ |
M|churn-prevention|| Hard decline recovery | <10% | 20-30% | 40%+ |
M|churn-prevention|| Overall payment recovery | <30% | 40-50% | 60%+ |
M|churn-prevention|| Pre-dunning prevention | None | 10-15% | 20-30% |
M|churn-prevention|For the complete dunning playbook with provider-specific setup, see [references/dunning-playbook.md](references/dunning-playbook.md).
M|churn-prevention|| Metric | Formula | Target |
M|churn-prevention||--------|---------|--------|
M|churn-prevention|| Monthly churn rate | Churned customers / Start-of-month customers | <5% B2C, <2% B2B |
M|churn-prevention|| Revenue churn (net) | (Lost MRR - Expansion MRR) / Start MRR | Negative (net expansion) |
M|churn-prevention|| Cancel flow save rate | Saved / Total cancel sessions | 25-35% |
M|churn-prevention|| Offer acceptance rate | Accepted offers / Shown offers | 15-25% |
M|churn-prevention|| Pause reactivation rate | Reactivated / Total paused | 60-80% |
M|churn-prevention|| Dunning recovery rate | Recovered / Total failed payments | 50-60% |
M|churn-prevention|| Time to cancel | Days from first churn signal to cancel | Track trend |
M|churn-prevention|Segment churn by:
M|churn-prevention|- **Acquisition channel** вҖ” Which channels bring stickier customers?
M|churn-prevention|- **Plan type** вҖ” Which plans churn most?
M|churn-prevention|- **Tenure** вҖ” When do most cancellations happen? (30, 60, 90 days?)
M|churn-prevention|- **Cancel reason** вҖ” Which reasons are growing?
M|churn-prevention|- **Save offer type** вҖ” Which offers work best for which segments?
M|churn-prevention|Test one variable at a time:
M|churn-prevention|| Test | Hypothesis | Metric |
M|churn-prevention||------|-----------|--------|
M|churn-prevention|| Discount % (20% vs 30%) | Higher discount saves more | Save rate, LTV impact |
M|churn-prevention|| Pause duration (1 vs 3 months) | Longer pause increases return rate | Reactivation rate |
M|churn-prevention|| Survey placement (before vs after offer) | Survey-first personalizes offers | Save rate |
M|churn-prevention|| Offer presentation (modal vs full page) | Full page gets more attention | Save rate |
M|churn-prevention|| Copy tone (empathetic vs direct) | Empathetic reduces friction | Save rate |
M|churn-prevention|**How to run cancel flow experiments:** Use the **ab-test-setup** skill to design statistically rigorous tests. PostHog is a good fit for cancel flow experiments вҖ” its feature flags can split users in
M|churn-prevention|- **No cancel flow at all** вҖ” Instant cancel leaves money on the table. Even a simple survey + one offer saves 10-15%
M|churn-prevention|- **Making cancellation hard to find** вҖ” Hidden cancel buttons breed resentment and bad reviews. Many jurisdictions require easy cancellation (FTC Click-to-Cancel rule)
M|churn-prevention|- **Same offer for every reason** вҖ” A blanket discount doesn't address "missing feature" or "not using it"
M|churn-prevention|- **Discounts too deep** вҖ” 50%+ discounts train customers to cancel-and-return for deals
M|churn-prevention|- **Ignoring involuntary churn** вҖ” Often 30-50% of total churn and the easiest to fix
M|churn-prevention|- **No dunning emails** вҖ” Letting payment failures silently cancel accounts
M|churn-prevention|- **Guilt-trip copy** вҖ” "Are you sure you want to abandon us?" damages brand trust
M|churn-prevention|- **Not tracking save offer LTV** вҖ” A "saved" customer who churns 30 days later wasn't really saved
M|churn-prevention|- **Pausing too long** вҖ” Pauses beyond 3 months rarely reactivate. Set limits.
M|churn-prevention|- **No post-cancel path** вҖ” Make reactivation easy and trigger win-back emails, because some churned users will want to come back
M|churn-prevention|For implementation, see the [tools registry](../../tools/REGISTRY.md).
M|churn-prevention|| Tool | Best For | Key Feature |
M|churn-prevention||------|----------|-------------|
M|churn-prevention|| **Churnkey** | Full cancel flow + dunning | AI-powered adaptive offers, 34% avg save rate |
M|churn-prevention|| **ProsperStack** | Cancel flows with anl | Advanced rules engine, Stripe/Chargebee integration |
M|churn-prevention|| **Raaft** | Simple cancel flow builder | Easy setup, good for early-stage |
M|churn-prevention|| **Chargebee Retention** | Chargebee customers | Native integration, was Brightback |
M|churn-prevention|| Provider | Smart Retries | Dunning Emails | Card Updater |
M|churn-prevention||----------|:------------:|:--------------:|:------------:|
M|churn-prevention|| **Stripe** | Built-in (Smart Retries) | Built-in | Automatic |
M|churn-prevention|| **Chargebee** | Built-in | Built-in | Via gateway |
M|churn-prevention|| **Paddle** | Built-in | Built-in | Managed |
M|churn-prevention|| **Recurly** | Built-in | Built-in | Built-in |
M|churn-prevention|| **Braintree** | Manual config | Manual | Via gateway |
M|churn-prevention|| Tool | Use For |
M|churn-prevention||------|---------|
M|churn-prevention|| `stripe` | Subscription management, dunning config, payment retries |
M|churn-prevention|| `customer-io` | Dunning email sequences, retention cg |
M|churn-prevention|| `posthog` | Cancel flow A/B tests via feature flags, funnel anl |
M|churn-prevention|| `mixpanel` / `ga4` | Usage tracking, churn signal analysis |
M|churn-prevention|| `segment` | Event routing for health scoring |
M|churn-prevention|- **email-sequence**: For win-back email sequences after cancellation
M|churn-prevention|- **paywall-upgrade-cro**: For in-app upgrade moments and trial expiration
M|churn-prevention|- **pricing-str**: For plan structure and annual discount str
M|churn-prevention|- **onboarding-cro**: For activation to prevent early churn
M|churn-prevention|- **anl-tracking**: For setting up churn signal events
M|churn-prevention|- **ab-test-setup**: For testing cancel flow variations with statistical rigor